labels.shortDescription: CLM - Understanding DocuSign CLM for Salesforce

labels.value: Managing Object Folders and Layout Configurations

labels.shortDescription: CLM - What Is DocuSign CLM for Salesforce?
labels.value: What is DocuSign CLM for Salesforce?

It's an app that connects your Salesforce data with DocuSign CLM. This lets you use your Salesforce data to create business documents. DocuSign CLM for Salesforce lets you store and manage those documents.

labels.shortDescription: CLM - Why DocuSign CLM for Salesforce
labels.value: Why should I use DocuSign CLM for Salesforce?
DocuSign CLM for Salesforce uses your Salesforce Data to generate documents. This speeds up document generation and removes the possibility of human error.
How does DocuSign CLM for Salesforce speed up my document generation process?
You can generate documents by pressing a single button in Salesforce. To do this, you'll have to create a custom button on your object page layouts.
Why should I use this app instead of storing my documents in Salesforce?

If you store documents in Salesforce they aren't organized and are hard to access. That slows down reviews, workflows and getting signatures. DocuSign CLM for Salesforce keeps things organized for you. It organizes documents automatically, even when you generate new documents. Plus, you can access your documents directly from Salesforce.

DocuSign CLM is the secure cloud app for DocuSign CLM for Salesforce. It lets you generate documents, collaborate with stakeholders and automate your processes. DocuSign CLM for Salesforce connects DocuSign CLM with your Salesforce org.

labels.shortDescription: CLM - Install DocuSign CLM for Salesforce
labels.value: How do I install DocuSign CLM for Salesforce?

labels.shortDescription: CLM - Install DocuSign Apps Launcher Answer
labels.value: First, go to the Salesforce AppExchange. Then search for the DocuSign Apps Launcher and follow the installation steps. You'll need to be a Salesforce administrator to do this.
How do I authenticate DocuSign CLM for Salesforce?

Open the DocuSign Apps Launcher in Salesforce after installation. Then sign in with your DocuSign CLM-enabled DocuSign login credentials and follow the the prompts to establish the reverse connection with your Salesforce credentials. This enables integration between the two systems.
Admins are users with special privileges and responsibilities in DocuSign CLM for Salesforce. Admins can map objects and manage users.
How do Admins add and manage users?

labels.shortDescription: CLM - How Admin Manage Users Answer
labels.value: Admins can add or manage users from the User Management page.
Do I have to pay extra fees per-user after installing the app?
No. The fees displayed on the AppExchange page show the general cost per-user if they purchased a DocuSign CLM package. There are no extra costs associated with installing any DocuSign apps.
Why should I configure a layout?
Configuring a layout will let you see your object folders in Salesforce and DocuSign CLM. This will then let you use your DocuSign CLM files and folders on your linked object pages.
What happens after I've mapped an object?
DocuSign CLM for Salesforce adds the object's data to your Visualforce library. To see the object's folders and files, you'll need to add them to any relevant Salesforce page layouts.

labels.shortDescription: CLM - Why Cannot See Object Folder
labels.value: Why can't I see my object folder?

labels.shortDescription: CLM - Cannot See Object Folder Answer
labels.value: If you're not seeing mapped objects, you likely need to edit your page layouts in Salesforce. You'll need to be a Salesforce Administrator to do this.
What are Salesforce objects and fields?

labels.shortDescription: CLM - Salesforce Objects And Fields Answer
labels.value: Salesforce objects are how Salesforce stores data. Every object has several associated fields containing data. To use objects and fields in DocuSign CLM for Salesforce, you'll first need to map your objects.
Object mapping is the process of connecting objects from your Salesforce org to DocuSign CLM. The DocuSign Apps Launcher setup walks you through the steps.
Why should I map my Salesforce objects?

DocuSign CLM for Salesforce needs the data in your objects to generate documents. Mapping your Salesforce objects is how you give access to that data. Only DocuSign CLM for Salesforce admins can map objects.
How do I map an Object?
To map your Salesforce objects, navigate to the CLM Integration page. Then select "Map New". Follow the prompts to complete setup.
You can edit or remove mapped objects from the CLM Integration page. Removing the object will mean you no longer can use the object's data for document generation.
Are there any standard objects I should map?

Every business is different and has different needs. "Account" and "Opportunity" are examples of standard objects that many businesses will use. DocuSign CLM for Salesforce maps those objects by default.
You can map custom Salesforce objects. To use custom objects you'll need to have created them in Salesforce first.
What should I name my Custom Object Folders?
Naming conventions are set by the object's merge fields. This process starts when you map your Salesforce objects. These folders' names will update whenever the contents of the fields change.
Why can't I just type in a name for my Custom Object Folders?

If you type in a name for those folders, then every instance of that object will have the same folder name. Salesforce doesn't allow duplicate folder names. That's why we recommend selecting a field instead.
Why do I need to choose a location for my object folder?
Choosing a location for your object folder keeps your documents organized.

You can always review these steps in the Help section. Look under "Generate an Agreement Using Salesforce Data" to find them.

labels.shortDescription: CLM - Map New Objects to DocuSign
labels.value: 1. Map new Salesforce objects to DocuSign CLM. You can also use the 'Account' and 'Opportunity' objects that we mapped for you.
2. Configure your Object page layout and add a folder portal component to see your object folders.
3. Go to DocuSign CLM and create a form using your mapped Salesforce object.
4. Use your created form to set up a document generation template in DocuSign CLM.
5. Copy the document generation configuration URL. Add to it a new button on your Saledforce object page layout.

labels.shortDescription: CLM - Generate Document on Single Click
labels.value: 6. Use that button to generate documents with a single click.
